\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the mandatory governance framework for the lifecycle management of Information Technology (IT) assets within Elko County.
 It ensures that technology resources—
hardware,
 software,
 and infrastructure—
are acquired,
 tracked,
 supported,
 optimized,
 and disposed of in a secure,
 fiscally responsible,
 and auditable manner.
 This policy serves as the authoritative basis for asset accountability,
 the prevention of waste,
 the reduction of security risk from lost or unauthorized equipment,
 and the maintenance of audit-ready records aligned with County procurement controls and system inventory requirements.
\end_layout

