\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the County’s Asset Steward and final approving authority for lifecycle standards,
 exceptions,
 and decommissioning determinations.
 Shall ensure the System Inventory is maintained as a mandatory security control (NIST CM-8,
 PM-5) and shall ensure annual reconciliation reporting is provided to Fiscal Affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Information Operations Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall execute asset management tasks,
 including receiving,
 tagging,
 CMDB/asset record maintenance,
 deployment,
 transfer processing,
 and secure decommissioning.
 Shall enforce the "No Tag,
 No Support" rule and shall deny onboarding for assets not registered in accordance with this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads (Asset Custodians)
\series default
:
 Shall act as Asset Custodians for assets assigned to their department.
 Shall maintain physical security of assets and ensure appropriate use.
 Shall ensure that no asset is transferred,
 relocated,
 or disposed of without processing through the Information Operations Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All County Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall protect assigned assets from theft or damage and shall promptly report loss,
 theft,
 or suspected compromise.
\end_layout

