\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Software and License Management
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Information Operations shall manage software assets to ensure license compliance and security.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Software Inventory
\series default
:
 Software,
 subscriptions,
 and SaaS entitlements shall be inventoried consistent with NIST CSF ID.AM-02.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
License Compliance
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall ensure license allocation is reconciled annually to prevent over-deployment (liability) or under-utilization (waste).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unapproved Software
\series default
:
 Installation of software or cloud services not recorded in the inventory is prohibited and subject to corrective action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Inventory Auditing and Reconciliation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Information Operations shall conduct inventory audits to validate record accuracy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Audit
\series default
:
 A physical and logical inventory validation shall be completed at least annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Reconciliation
\series default
:
 Discrepancies between the physical audit and the CMDB shall be investigated and reconciled within thirty (30) calendar days of discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fiscal Reporting
\series default
:
 Information Operations shall provide an annual asset reconciliation report to Fiscal Affairs to support County financial reporting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Movement and Transfer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To preserve inventory integrity,
 assets shall not be transferred between users,
 relocated between facilities,
 or reassigned without an approved Service Request and corresponding CMDB update.
 Unauthorized relocation of assets by custodians is prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9 Secure Storage and Loss Reporting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Custodians shall ensure assets are stored securely.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Physical Security
\series default
:
 Storage practices for assets capable of accessing or storing Criminal Justice Information (CJI) shall align with 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy Section 5.9.1
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Incident Reporting
\series default
:
 Lost,
 stolen,
 or potentially compromised assets shall be reported to Information Operations immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Reporting Requirement
\series default
:
 If a lost or stolen device contains or has access to CJI,
 the incident shall be reported to the IT Director (LASO) immediately,
 and no later than one (1) hour after discovery,
 and additional incident details shall be provided as soon as possible.
 If the incident is confirmed,
 the IT Director (LASO) shall ensure required CJIS notifications are made to the CSO,
 SIB Chief,
 or Interface Agency Official,
 as applicable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.10 Secure Disposal and Decommissioning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Information Operations shall control decommissioning to prevent data exposure and ensure auditable disposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sanitization Standard
\series default
:
 All digital media shall be sanitized prior to disposal,
 release,
 or reuse using methods (Clear,
 Purge,
 or Destroy) consistent with 
\series bold
NIST SP 800-88 Rev.
 1
\series default
 and 
\series bold
Policy 
