.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Method Selection
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall approve the sanitization method based on the classification of data stored on the device.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Documentation
\series default
:
 Sanitization and disposal actions shall be documented,
 including the date,
 method used,
 and the personnel performing the validation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
E-Waste
\series default
:
 Electronic waste shall be transferred only through approved recycling vendors that provide certificates of destruction/recycling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.11 Offsite and Home Use
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
County IT assets are intended for County business use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorized Offsite Use
\series default
:
 Only portable devices (laptops,
 tablets,
 smartphones) issued to a specific user are authorized for offsite use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Removal
\series default
:
 Infrastructure,
 desktop computers,
 printers,
 and monitors shall not be removed from County premises for home use without written exception approval from the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Liability
\series default
:
 Assets used offsite are subject to the same acceptable use and security policies as onsite equipment.
\end_layout

